      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (NIH, shear stress distribution, residence time) are directly linked to the decision question of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis is the regulatory QoI for CPB hemolysis assessment. Shear stress and residence time are mechanistically linked to red cell damage. All QoIs are decision-relevant. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
